# Copy to `.env` (gitignored). All values are optional.

# Capability secret for a PRIVATE network. Peers land in the same Hyperswarm
# room only if they share the same salt: the topic is derived as
# sha256(topicPrefix + salt || roomId), so a non-empty salt yields a topic
# that cannot be computed from the public source code.
#
#   empty / unset  -> the public Resonance network (default)
#   any shared value -> a private network for exactly the devices that set it
#
# Use a high-entropy value (e.g. 32 random bytes hex: in PowerShell
# `-join ((1..32) | ForEach-Object { '{0:x2}' -f (Get-Random -Max 256) })`); a guessable
# salt is brute-forceable offline.
EXPO_PUBLIC_NETWORK_SALT=
